MORE INFROMATIONS.....
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Creating/Loading a new Musicmodule.....
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

This version of F.I.M. can handle Soundmods. created with the Musicprg.
`PROTRACKER` or a ClonePrg. like Sound/Noisetracker....
When using a CloneMusicprg., a can`t promise the correctly Replay of the tune,
because the Song/Sample-Effects are`nt the same in all the different versions
of this MusicPrg..

You also should note that the module may NOT be longer than MAX. 32KBYTE !!!


The Amount of incoming Shareware-Fees and UserFeedbacks will decide if its
necessary to release a new Version of the FastIntroMaker, wich will be able
to handle more and bigger (KByte) SoundModul-Types.


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Creating a Demo-Text.....
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Well, to create a Demotext, just load your favourite Texteditor (maybe ED)
and type some nice sentences...

But remember that the Text should not include more than 31LINES. Longer Texts
will be cutted (F.I.M. only loads in the first 31 Lines of you TextFile).

Also note that the lines should not contain more than 40CHRAS. Longer lines
will also be cutted (The Rest will be typed in the next line).

Just create some Demotext and see what happens..... The Text in the Intro
will be displayed as in the F.I.M. Text-Display on the right Screenside.

To use Special-Chars, look in the upper listed Char-Tab.


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Creating a Demo-Text.....
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Puhhh.... to create a Demopic, just paint a Pic with your ???-Paintprg. and
load it into F.I.M..

But remember before painting.. The PictureFormat MUST be: IFF 320×256 8Colors
Okay.... thats it......


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Saving a BootBlock-Demo to Disk.....
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

To save the current Demo as a Bootblockdemo you`ll need a empty DOS-Disk.

EMPTY.... Yes, the Disk should be empty, because F.I.M. will write the
          Intro from the first Diskblock on. Any Files on the Disk, which
          are located on these Blocks will be corrupted.

DOS...... Finaly you`ll need a DOS-Disk, because after writing the Intro
          to Disk, F.I.M. wants to update/remap the Disk-Bitmapblock.
          If no DiskBitmap is available F.I.M. will pop up a ErrorRequester.


A LITTLE EXAMPLE.....


1).
Take a fresh formated Disk, put it in your Diskdrive called DF0: and press
the `SAVE BOOTINTRO` Gadget.

2.)
A Requester comes up asking you to include or leave the current MusicModule.
When leaving the Music, the Intro will be shorter (about 32KB).

3.)
The final Requester pops up waiting for your command to install the Disk in
DF0: (INSTALL DF0:) or to abort the whole Action (ABORT OPERATION).

4.)
When installing the Intro, look at the Drive-Lamp/LED. When the Diskdrive
has stopped, the Disk is installed. Now you can quit F.I.M. or do anything.


ATTENTION VIRUSKILLER:
----------------------
Some Viruskiller don`t allow other Progs. to install a new Bootblock on Disk.
When installing your Intro to Disk, try to remove your active Viruskiller for
this operation.


